The binary distribution for Windows had some problems with missing 
DLL files. This has now been fixed. 
An updated version of the Cantera Python interface for Windows is 
available at 
http://blue.caltech.edu/cantera_dist/1.3/win32/PyCantera13.msi

Also, I have put the Python installation programs at 
http://blue.caltech.edu/cantera_dist/Python. If you don't have Python 
and NumPy, run both of these (Python first) before installing Cantera.
